y among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705188,"age":4,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705189,"age":39,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705190,"age":70,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"William Leveson was born about 1220, in Willenhall, Staffordshire, England. He married Mrs William Leveson in 1240. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1300, at the age of 81."},"et":{"about 1219–1300":"umbes 1220–1300","1225–Female":"1225–Surnud","1241–1300":"1241–1300","1220–1300":"1220–1300","about 1219":"umbes 1220","1259":"1259","1225":"1225","1224":"1224","1300":"1300","1220":"1220","1241":"1241","1240":"1240","about 1300":"umbes 1300","about 1241":"umbes 1241","1290":"1290","Willenhall, Staffordshire, England":"Willenhall, Staffordshire, England"},"fi":{"about 1219–1300":"noin 1220–1300","1225–Female":"1225–Kuollut","1241–1300":"1241–1300","1220–1300":"1220–1300","about 1219":"noin 1220","1259":"1259","1225":"1225","1224":"1224","1300":"1300","1220":"1220","1241":"1241","1240":"1240","about 1300":"noin 1300","about 1241":"noin 1241","1290":"1290","Willenhall, Staffordshire, England":"Willenhall, Staffor